codex
**Mechanism Hypothesis**

D3D9 does not appear to latch the player/camera transform at a different alter/render boundary than D3D11. Both backends read after `Game::runGameLoopOnce()` finishes update/alter and enters draw. The vulnerable state is shared simulation state: portal crossing flips `parentCell` immediately inside `positionChanged()`, while Y is corrected later by collision/floor-follow (`Footprint::snapObjectToGround()` / `snapToCellFloor()`). If that later ground snap is missed, delayed, or performed from stale floor contacts on the exit frame, render reads a legitimate-but-transient cell-relative transform.

D3D9 then makes that transient visible because its per-object WVP is composed lazily at draw from the currently cached object/world/camera matrices. D3D11 follows the same logical timing, but uploads through its slot-0 shadow/dirty path; I do not see evidence of an earlier/later transform latch that would make D3D9 uniquely wrong.

**File:Line Evidence**

Frame order:

- `src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/core/Game.cpp:1092` reads `Clock::frameTime()`.
- `Game.cpp:1181` runs `CuiManager::update(elapsedTime)` before drawing.
- `Game.cpp:1207-1227` runs `Graphics::update`, `beginScene`, `IoWinManager::draw`, `endScene`, then `Graphics::present`.

Player/cell/Y writers:

- `src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/controller/PlayerCreatureController.cpp:1114` / `:1119` writes movement via `setPosition_w(...)`.
- `src/engine/shared/library/sharedObject/src/shared/object/Object.h:715-719` `setPosition_p()` writes parent-space position and calls `positionChanged`.
- `Object.h:729-734` `setPosition_w()` converts world to parent and calls `setPosition_p`.
- `src/engine/shared/library/sharedObject/src/shared/portal/CellProperty.cpp:116-204` portal walk detects crossing and calls `object.setParentCell(targetCell)`.
- `src/engine/shared/library/sharedObject/src/shared/object/Object.cpp:1387-1408` `setParentCell()` detaches to world, then `attachToObject_w()` into the new cell.
- `Object.cpp:1956-1970` `attachToObject_w()` recomputes `m_objectToParent.position` from current world position in the new parent frame.
- `src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/CollisionWorld.cpp:633` zeroes collision delta Y.
- `CollisionWorld.cpp:776` calls `foot->snapObjectToGround()`.
- `src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/Footprint.cpp:1079-1088` `snapObjectToGround()` writes object Y to `m_groundHeight`.
- `Footprint.cpp:897-909` `snapToCellFloor()` can reattach to the cell floor.
- `src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/CollisionResolve.cpp:337` collision rewind writes `resetPos`; per CONSULT-43 this is not required for the no-resolve exit snap, but it is another Y writer.

Transform reads/latches for render:

- `src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/camera/FreeChaseCamera.cpp:604-628` chase camera copies target `parentCell` and `targetObject->getTransform_o2c()` during camera alter.
- `src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/shared/Camera.cpp:629-637` `Camera::applyState()` reads `getTransform_o2w()`, inverts it, calls `Graphics::setWorldToCameraTransform`.
- `src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/shared/RenderWorld.cpp:855-884` `RenderWorld::drawScene()` reads camera `parentCell`, `getTransform_o2w()`, and `getTransform_o2c()`.
- `src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/shared/RenderWorldCommander.cpp:344` and `:409` read each visible object’s `getTransform_o2w()` into `Appearance::setTransform_w()`.
- `src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9.cpp:3271-3290` D3D9 caches world-to-camera and camera position.
- `Direct3d9.cpp:3402-3414` D3D9 caches object-to-world and marks transform dirty.
- `Direct3d9.cpp:4030-4038` D3D9 composes/uploads object WVP at draw when dirty.
- `src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:1868-1923` D3D11 caches view/camera and composes slot-0 shadow.
- `Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:2022-2065` D3D11 caches object-to-world and composes shadow.
- `Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:1265-1275` `applyPreDrawState()` flushes dirty slot-0 before draw.

**Empirical Discriminator**

Add one paired Debug log at the four shared handoff points on the door-exit frame: after `CellProperty.cpp:204` parent flip, after `Footprint.cpp:1088` ground snap, inside `Camera::applyState()`, and in each backend’s per-object WVP upload (`Direct3d9.cpp:4038`, D3D11 `flushSlot0IfDirty`). Log frame, player cell, player world Y, camera cell/world Y, and the matrix translation.

Prediction: if my hypothesis is right, D3D9 and D3D11 receive the same shared transient when it exists; the differentiator is whether the transient survives to render, not a D3D9-only earlier latch.
